  "text": "The benefit of immune tolerance was further demonstrated in Gaucher disease mice. An AAV2/8 vector containing a liver-specific regulatory cassette secreted human glucocerebrosidase continuously, which prevented glucosylceramide accumulations and the appearance of Gaucher cells in the liver, spleen, and lungs [CITATION_1] . A challenge with recombinant glucocerebrosidase failed to provoke antibody formation in vector-treated mice, whereas mock-treated mice formed high-titer antibodies in response to enzyme administration. This experiment suggested the possibility that gene therapy might actually improve the benefit of ERT.",
